ENTRY            31873   20260420   20260528   20260528       3223
SUBENT        31873001   20260420   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                 16         50
TITLE      Experimental reevaluation of 235U fission yields at
            the Egypt second research reactor (ETRR-2)
AUTHOR     (Nader M.A.Mohamed, Fatma S.Abdou, Abdullah M.Othman,
            Mohamed A.Elsaied, M.Shabib, Asmaa G.Abo Elnour,
            D.H.Daher, M.Soliman)
INSTITUTE  (3EGYCAI)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,113,034604,2026)
FACILITY   (REAC,3EGYCAI) 22 MW power reactor (ETRR-2)
SAMPLE     Ten subsamples of natural UO2 (each 6.5 mg) were
            mixed with about 6 mg Na2CO3 powder of Na as an
            internal comparator. Triple bare flux monitors of
            Au-Zr (99% pure) were prepared for neutron flux.
            Two pure Na2CO3 samples used for investigate the
            concentration of sodium in the compound using neutron
            activation analysis and ~0.5 g of UO2 sample was
            prepared for natural activity measurements.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Detector with relative efficiency of 100% and
            2.1 keV energy resolution for 1332 keV gamma-line of
            60Co line.
METHOD     (ACTIV) For short-lived the neutron flux was
            3.787 X 10**12 n/cm2/sec and time of irradiation was
             20 sec for each sample and 60 sec for flux monitor,
            while for long-lived fission products the neutron flux
            was (3.07-2.6) X 10**12 n/cm2/sec and irradiation time
            was 2.5 hr.
MONITOR    (11-NA-23(N,G)11-NA-24,,SIG)
DECAY-MON  (11-NA-24,14.956HR,DG,1368.6,0.99994)
ASSUMED    (ASSUM,92-U-235(N,F),,SIG)
ANALYSIS   Samples of 235U and 23Na are irradiated in the same
            neutron flux, and the gamma activities are measured.
            The thermal fission cross section of 235U and the
            thermal capture cross section of 23Na are taken from
            standard nuclear data libraries (ENDF/B-VIII.1,
            JEFF-3.3, and JENDL-5) and averaged, with the
            uncertainty taken as the standard deviation. Using the
            Westcott method, with a factor of 1.001 for 23Na and
            0.9803 +/- 0.0007 for 235U, the ratio of their
            activities is calculated, and after applying decay
            corrections, the fission yield from the 235U(n,f)
            reaction is obtained.
CORRECTION Corrected for:
           . Self-absorption
           . Geometry effects
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Uncertainty due to replicated measurements
           (ERR-1) Detector efficiency (1%)
           (ERR-2,,1.) Monte Carlo-based correction factors (<1%)
STATUS     (APRVD) Proof-read by Nader M.A.Mohamed (2026-04-27)
           (TABLE,,Nader M.A.Mohamed+,J,PR/C,113,034604,2026)
            Table IV and decay data from Supplemental material.
HISTORY    (20260420C) VT
ENDBIB              50
COMMON               7          6
EN-DUMMY   ERR-1      EN-NRM     MONIT      MONIT-ERR  ASSUM
ASSUM-ERR
EV         PER-CENT   EV         B          B          B
B
     0.0253         1.     0.0253     0.5278     0.0039      585.8
        1.1
ENDCOMMON            6
ENDSUBENT           60
SUBENT        31873002   20260420   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                  2        667
REACTION   (92-U-235(N,F)ELEM/MASS,CUM,FY,,SPA)
